WEBVTT



00:00:00.512 --> 00:00:09.920
Hello friends, I'm Rick Warren and welcome to Spurgeon's Sermons. This is the official podcast brought to you by Premier and Spurgeon's College.

00:00:09.856 --> 00:00:19.904
You know, the teachings of Charles Spurgeon have had a personal impact on my life in a profound way, and I'm confident they'll do the same for you. So get ready to be challenged.

00:00:19.424 --> 00:00:28.192
be challenged, equipped, and guided by Charles Spurgeon, who is universally regarded as the greatest English preacher in the history of the Church.

00:00:28.960 --> 00:00:31.520
Supposing him to be the gardener.

00:00:32.064 --> 00:00:35.328
A sermon by Charles Spurgeon, part four.

00:00:35.968 --> 00:00:38.656
Supposing him to be the gardener.

00:00:39.488 --> 00:00:41.856
John's Gospel chapter 20

00:00:41.728 --> 00:00:43.232
Verse 15

00:00:44.544 --> 00:00:47.648
I am sometimes troubled by the question:

00:00:47.424 --> 00:00:52.096
What if roots of bitterness should spring up among us to trouble us?

00:00:52.512 --> 00:00:55.424
We're all such fallible creatures.

00:00:55.392 --> 00:01:00.608
Supposing some brother should permit the seed of discord to grow in his bosom.

00:01:01.056 --> 00:01:03.008
Then there may be a sister,

00:01:02.784 --> 00:01:06.176
In whose heart the seeds will also spring up.

00:01:06.400 --> 00:01:09.568
And from her they will fly to another sister.

00:01:09.472 --> 00:01:16.160
And be blown about till brethren and sisters are all bearing rue and wormwood in their hearts.

00:01:16.352 --> 00:01:18.368
Who is to prevent this?

00:01:19.136 --> 00:01:22.304
Only the Lord Jesus by his spirit.

00:01:23.104 --> 00:01:25.696
He can keep out this evil.

00:01:25.760 --> 00:01:28.384
Supposing him to be the gardener.

00:01:29.056 --> 00:01:32.704
The root which bears wormwood will grow but little.

00:01:32.512 --> 00:01:34.048
Where Jesus is.

00:01:34.432 --> 00:01:36.384
Dwell with us, Lord.

00:01:36.256 --> 00:01:38.464
As a church and people.

00:01:38.432 --> 00:01:42.752
By your holy spirit reside with us and in us.

00:01:42.784 --> 00:01:45.024
And never depart from us.

00:01:45.056 --> 00:01:49.728
And then no root of bitterness shall spring up to trouble us.

00:01:50.368 --> 00:01:52.320
Then comes another fear.

00:01:52.480 --> 00:01:58.016
Supposing the living waters of God's Spirit should not come to water the garden.

00:01:58.304 --> 00:01:59.488
What then?

00:01:59.904 --> 00:02:03.616
We cannot make them flow, for the spirit is a sovereign.

00:02:03.808 --> 00:02:06.176
And he flows where he pleases.

00:02:07.040 --> 00:02:13.760
Ah, but the spirit of God will be in our garden, supposing our Lord to be the gardener.

00:02:14.432 --> 00:02:17.440
There is no fear of our not being watered.

00:02:17.344 --> 00:02:19.872
when Jesus undertakes to do it.

00:02:20.544 --> 00:02:24.256
He will pour water on him that is thirsty.

00:02:24.512 --> 00:02:27.104
And floods upon the dry ground.

00:02:27.776 --> 00:02:32.192
But what if the sunlight of his love should not shine on the garden?

00:02:32.224 --> 00:02:34.816
If the fruits should never ripen

00:02:34.848 --> 00:02:37.184
If there should be no peace,

00:02:36.992 --> 00:02:39.008
No joy in the Lord.

00:02:39.264 --> 00:02:41.312
That cannot happen.

00:02:41.344 --> 00:02:43.904
Supposing him to be the gardener.

00:02:44.576 --> 00:02:47.072
For his face is the sun.

00:02:47.328 --> 00:02:53.536
And his countenance scatters those health-giving beams and nurturing warmths.

00:02:53.536 --> 00:02:58.752
And perfecting influences which are needful for maturing the saints.

00:02:58.816 --> 00:03:02.752
In all the sweetness of grace to the glory of God.

00:03:03.904 --> 00:03:08.768
So supposing him to be the gardener at this the close of the year,

00:03:08.736 --> 00:03:14.368
I fling away my doubts and fears and invite you who bear the church upon your heart.

00:03:14.208 --> 00:03:15.712
To do the same.

00:03:16.384 --> 00:03:19.552
It is all well with Christ's cause.

00:03:19.488 --> 00:03:22.464
Because it is in his own hands.

00:03:22.592 --> 00:03:24.288
He shall not fail.

00:03:24.128 --> 00:03:26.016
Nor be discouraged.

00:03:26.464 --> 00:03:30.496
The pleasure of the Lord shall prosper in his hands.

00:03:31.104 --> 00:03:32.448
Fifthly,

00:03:32.384 --> 00:03:34.944
Here is a warning for the careless.

00:03:35.264 --> 00:03:37.888
Supposing him to be the gardener.

00:03:38.464 --> 00:03:42.464
In this great congregation, many are to the church.

00:03:42.240 --> 00:03:44.992
What weeds are to a garden.

00:03:45.472 --> 00:03:48.128
They are not planted by God.

00:03:48.032 --> 00:03:50.848
They are not growing under his nurture.

00:03:51.424 --> 00:03:54.752
They are bringing forth no fruit to his glory.

00:03:55.424 --> 00:03:57.152
My dear friend,

00:03:57.056 --> 00:03:59.840
I have tried often to get at you.

00:03:59.680 --> 00:04:01.312
To impress you

00:04:01.600 --> 00:04:02.976
But I cannot.

00:04:03.520 --> 00:04:04.832
Take heed.

00:04:04.704 --> 00:04:08.320
For one of these days, supposing him to be the gardener.

00:04:08.512 --> 00:04:10.048
He will reach you.

00:04:10.144 --> 00:04:13.056
And you shall know what the word means.

00:04:12.928 --> 00:04:17.152
Every plant which my heavenly Father hath not planted,

00:04:17.216 --> 00:04:18.816
Shall be rooted up,

00:04:19.936 --> 00:04:22.912
Take heed to yourselves, I pray.

00:04:24.416 --> 00:04:25.952
Others among us

00:04:25.728 --> 00:04:29.280
Are like the branches of the vine which bear no fruit.

00:04:29.568 --> 00:04:32.960
We have often spoken very sharply to these.

00:04:32.704 --> 00:04:35.104
Speaking honest truth

00:04:34.976 --> 00:04:37.440
In unmistakable language.

00:04:37.504 --> 00:04:40.704
And yet we have not touched their consciences.

00:04:41.376 --> 00:04:44.192
But supposing him to be the gardener,

00:04:44.416 --> 00:04:46.976
He will fulfill that sentence.

00:04:47.008 --> 00:04:50.176
Every branch in me that beareth not fruit,

00:04:50.144 --> 00:04:51.776
He taketh away.

00:04:51.840 --> 00:04:53.696
He will get at you.

00:04:53.760 --> 00:04:55.456
If we cannot.

00:04:56.384 --> 00:05:00.256
Would God ere this old year were quite dead?

00:05:00.192 --> 00:05:04.096
You would turn unto the Lord with full purpose of heart.

00:05:04.224 --> 00:05:06.624
So that instead of being a weed,

00:05:06.560 --> 00:05:08.992
You might become a choice flower.

00:05:09.376 --> 00:05:11.808
That instead of a dry stick

00:05:12.128 --> 00:05:16.096
You might be a sappy, fruit-bearing branch of the vine.

00:05:16.992 --> 00:05:19.104
The Lord make it to be so.

00:05:19.712 --> 00:05:22.176
But if any here need the caution

00:05:22.048 --> 00:05:25.248
I pray them to take it to heart at once.

00:05:25.376 --> 00:05:27.904
Supposing him to be the gardener,

00:05:27.776 --> 00:05:30.784
There will be no escaping from his eye.

00:05:31.104 --> 00:05:34.208
There will be no deliverance from his hand.

00:05:34.816 --> 00:05:36.576
As he will thoroughly,

00:05:36.416 --> 00:05:39.040
Purge his floor and burn up.

00:05:38.976 --> 00:05:40.160
The chaff.

00:05:40.000 --> 00:05:42.016
With unquenchable fire.

00:05:42.496 --> 00:05:45.280
So he will thoroughly cleanse his garden.

00:05:45.248 --> 00:05:48.448
And cast out every worthless thing.

00:05:49.504 --> 00:05:54.816
Another set of thoughts may well arise as a quietus to those who complain.

00:05:54.880 --> 00:05:57.152
Supposing him to be the gardener.

00:05:57.952 --> 00:05:59.488
Certain of us,

00:05:59.392 --> 00:06:02.816
Have been made to suffer much physical pain.

00:06:03.040 --> 00:06:05.856
Which often bites into the spirits.

00:06:06.016 --> 00:06:08.320
And makes the heart to stoop.

00:06:09.280 --> 00:06:12.704
Others have suffered heavy temporal losses.

00:06:12.864 --> 00:06:15.424
Having had no success in business.

00:06:15.968 --> 00:06:17.472
But on the contrary,

00:06:17.408 --> 00:06:20.064
Have had to endure privation.

00:06:19.840 --> 00:06:22.784
Perhaps even to extreme poverty.

00:06:23.488 --> 00:06:27.552
Are you ready to complain against the Lord for all this?

00:06:28.224 --> 00:06:30.272
I pray you do not so.

00:06:31.200 --> 00:06:35.136
Take the supposition of the text into your mind this morning.

00:06:35.264 --> 00:06:38.432
The Lord has been pruning you sharply.

00:06:38.432 --> 00:06:40.960
Cutting off your best bows

00:06:40.992 --> 00:06:44.064
And you seem to be like a thing despised.

00:06:44.000 --> 00:06:47.168
That is constantly tormented with the knife.

00:06:47.424 --> 00:06:48.416
Yes.

00:06:48.160 --> 00:06:49.056
But,

00:06:48.704 --> 00:06:51.488
Supposing him to be the gardener?

00:06:51.616 --> 00:06:55.200
Suppose that your loving Lord has wrought it all.

00:06:55.616 --> 00:06:59.136
That from his own hand all your grief has come.

00:06:59.808 --> 00:07:01.088
Every cut

00:07:01.056 --> 00:07:02.784
And every gash

00:07:02.592 --> 00:07:04.032
And every slip,

00:07:04.672 --> 00:07:07.200
Does not this alter the case?

00:07:07.712 --> 00:07:10.016
Hath not the Lord done it?

00:07:10.816 --> 00:07:13.088
Well, then, if it be so,

00:07:12.928 --> 00:07:15.136
Put your finger to your lip.

00:07:14.944 --> 00:07:16.288
And be quiet.

00:07:16.768 --> 00:07:20.128
Until you are able from your heart to say

00:07:19.968 --> 00:07:21.376
The Lord gave,

00:07:21.312 --> 00:07:23.712
And the Lord hath taken away.

00:07:23.840 --> 00:07:26.560
And blessed be the name of the lord

00:07:27.520 --> 00:07:31.360
I am persuaded that the Lord hath done nothing amiss.

00:07:31.264 --> 00:07:33.216
To any one of his people.

00:07:33.600 --> 00:07:35.840
That no child of his,

00:07:35.552 --> 00:07:40.224
Can rightly complain that he has been whipped with too much severity.

00:07:41.056 --> 00:07:43.904
And that no one branch of the vine,

00:07:43.776 --> 00:07:45.792
Can truthfully declare

00:07:45.600 --> 00:07:49.216
That it has been pruned with too sharp an edge.

00:07:49.440 --> 00:07:50.368
No.

00:07:51.072 --> 00:07:55.328
What the Lord has done is the best that could have been done.

00:07:55.584 --> 00:07:58.336
The very thing that you and I,

00:07:58.208 --> 00:08:01.568
If we could have possessed infinite wisdom and love

00:08:01.664 --> 00:08:03.904
Would have wished to have done.

00:08:04.256 --> 00:08:07.584
Therefore let us stop each thought of murmuring.

00:08:07.520 --> 00:08:10.016
And say, The Lord hath done it.

00:08:10.112 --> 00:08:11.488
And be glad.

00:08:13.088 --> 00:08:16.864
Especially, I speak to those who have suffered bereavement.

00:08:17.280 --> 00:08:21.408
I can hardly express to you how strange I feel at this moment.

00:08:21.568 --> 00:08:24.864
When my sermon revives a memory so sweet

00:08:24.800 --> 00:08:26.016
Dashed

00:08:26.016 --> 00:08:28.576
With such exceeding bitterness.

00:08:29.632 --> 00:08:32.736
I sat with my friend and secretary.

00:08:32.640 --> 00:08:35.968
in that garden some 15 days ago.

00:08:36.192 --> 00:08:38.432
And we were then in perfect health,

00:08:38.304 --> 00:08:40.864
Rejoicing in the goodness of the Lord.

00:08:41.280 --> 00:08:42.976
We returned home.

00:08:42.912 --> 00:08:47.360
And within five days I was smitten with disabling pain.

00:08:47.904 --> 00:08:50.464
And worse, far worse than that.

00:08:50.464 --> 00:08:53.248
He was called upon to lose his wife.

00:08:53.792 --> 00:08:59.104
We said to one another as we sat there reading the word of God and meditating.

00:08:59.264 --> 00:09:00.960
How happy we are!

00:09:01.440 --> 00:09:04.224
Dare we think of being so happy?

00:09:04.928 --> 00:09:07.360
Must it not speedily end?

00:09:08.032 --> 00:09:14.464
I little thought I should have to say for him, alas, my brother, thou art brought very low.

00:09:14.688 --> 00:09:18.272
For the delight of thine eyes is taken from thee.

00:09:19.392 --> 00:09:21.216
But here is our comfort,

00:09:21.824 --> 00:09:23.808
The Lord hath done it.

00:09:24.640 --> 00:09:27.904
The best rose in the garden is gone.

00:09:28.512 --> 00:09:30.080
Who has taken it?

00:09:30.720 --> 00:09:32.000
The gardener

00:09:32.096 --> 00:09:34.208
Came this way and gathered it.

00:09:34.560 --> 00:09:36.160
He planted it.

00:09:35.936 --> 00:09:37.632
And watched over it.

00:09:37.504 --> 00:09:39.488
And now he has taken it.

00:09:40.128 --> 00:09:42.400
Is not this most natural?

00:09:43.104 --> 00:09:44.640
Does anybody weep?

00:09:44.896 --> 00:09:46.176
Because of that.

00:09:46.752 --> 00:09:49.760
No, everybody knows that it is right.

00:09:49.856 --> 00:09:52.704
And according to the order of nature,

00:09:52.608 --> 00:09:56.064
That he should come and gather the best in the garden.

00:09:57.344 --> 00:10:00.800
If you are so troubled by the loss of your beloved,

00:10:01.088 --> 00:10:05.440
Yet dry your grief by supposing him to be the gardener.

00:10:06.784 --> 00:10:10.624
Kiss the hand that has wrought you such grief.

00:10:11.296 --> 00:10:12.960
Brothers and sisters,

00:10:12.992 --> 00:10:17.248
Remember the next time the Lord comes to your part of the garden.

00:10:17.088 --> 00:10:19.808
And he may do so within the next week.

00:10:20.384 --> 00:10:23.232
He will only gather his own flowers.

00:10:23.680 --> 00:10:27.136
And would you prevent his doing so even if you could?

00:10:28.736 --> 00:10:31.168
Supposing him to be the gardener,

00:10:31.680 --> 00:10:33.760
Then there is an outlook.

00:10:33.472 --> 00:10:34.976
Look for the hopeful.

00:10:35.776 --> 00:10:38.560
Supposing him to be the gardener, then?

00:10:38.368 --> 00:10:41.760
I expect to see in the garden where he works.

00:10:41.568 --> 00:10:44.256
The best possible prosperity.

00:10:44.608 --> 00:10:47.680
I expect to see no flower dried up.

00:10:47.840 --> 00:10:49.984
No tree without fruit.

00:10:50.784 --> 00:10:54.240
I expect to see the richest, rarest fruit.

00:10:54.176 --> 00:10:56.736
With the daintiest bloom upon it,

00:10:56.704 --> 00:11:00.320
Daily presented to the great owner of the garden.

00:11:01.248 --> 00:11:04.160
Let us expect that in this church.

00:11:04.000 --> 00:11:05.632
And pray for it.

00:11:06.560 --> 00:11:08.960
Oh, if we have but faith.

00:11:08.928 --> 00:11:11.232
We shall see great things.

00:11:11.616 --> 00:11:13.408
It is our unbelief.

00:11:13.440 --> 00:11:15.424
That straightens God.

00:11:16.256 --> 00:11:21.536
Let us believe great things from the work of Christ, by his Spirit.

00:11:21.408 --> 00:11:23.968
In the midst of his people's hearts,

00:11:23.808 --> 00:11:26.112
And we shall not be disappointed.

00:11:27.360 --> 00:11:30.976
Supposing him to be the gardener then, dear friends?

00:11:31.040 --> 00:11:36.000
We may expect divine intercourse of unspeakable preciousness.

00:11:36.736 --> 00:11:39.040
Go back to Eden for a minute.

00:11:39.808 --> 00:11:42.048
When Adam was the gardener,

00:11:42.144 --> 00:11:43.424
What happened?

00:11:44.288 --> 00:11:47.808
The Lord God walked in the garden in the cool of the day.

00:11:48.416 --> 00:11:51.296
But supposing him to be the gardener?

00:11:51.520 --> 00:11:54.816
Then we shall have the Lord God dwelling among us.

00:11:54.784 --> 00:11:58.400
And revealing himself in all the glory of his power.

00:11:58.400 --> 00:12:01.280
And the plenitude of his fatherly heart.

00:12:01.600 --> 00:12:03.520
Making us to know him.

00:12:03.616 --> 00:12:06.976
That we may be filled with all the fullness of God.

00:12:06.912 --> 00:12:09.248
What joy is this?

00:12:10.784 --> 00:12:12.160
One other thought.

00:12:13.184 --> 00:12:15.744
Supposing him to be the gardener,

00:12:15.680 --> 00:12:19.648
And gods to come and walk among the trees of the garden.

00:12:20.256 --> 00:12:27.456
Then I expect he will remove the whole of the garden upward with himself to fairer skies.

00:12:27.936 --> 00:12:29.632
For he rose,

00:12:29.728 --> 00:12:32.384
And his people must rise with him.

00:12:32.960 --> 00:12:37.280
I expect a blessed transplanting of all these flowers below.

00:12:37.408 --> 00:12:40.000
To a clearer atmosphere above.

00:12:40.576 --> 00:12:43.936
Away from all this smoke and fog

00:12:43.776 --> 00:12:44.992
And damp.

00:12:45.312 --> 00:12:47.936
Up where the sun is never clouded.

00:12:48.320 --> 00:12:50.336
Where flowers never wither

00:12:50.624 --> 00:12:53.120
Where fruits never decay.

00:12:54.016 --> 00:12:57.568
O the glory, we shall then enjoy up yonder,

00:12:57.568 --> 00:12:59.968
On the hills of spices,

00:12:59.808 --> 00:13:01.760
In the garden of God,

00:13:02.304 --> 00:13:04.960
Supposing him to be the gardener,

00:13:04.704 --> 00:13:07.456
What a garden will he form above!

00:13:07.648 --> 00:13:10.784
And how shall you and I grow therein?

00:13:10.816 --> 00:13:13.568
Developing beyond imagination.

00:13:14.592 --> 00:13:17.824
It doth not yet appear what we shall be.

00:13:18.144 --> 00:13:19.392
But we know.

00:13:19.456 --> 00:13:22.624
That when he shall appear, we shall be like him.

00:13:22.976 --> 00:13:25.568
For we shall see him as he is.

00:13:26.368 --> 00:13:30.400
Since he is the author and finisher of our faith,

00:13:30.656 --> 00:13:34.048
To what perfection will he conduct us?

00:13:34.208 --> 00:13:37.312
And to what glory will he bring us?

00:13:37.568 --> 00:13:39.904
Oh, to be found in him!

00:13:40.000 --> 00:13:42.336
God grant that we may be.

00:13:43.072 --> 00:13:45.824
To be plants in his garden.

00:13:46.112 --> 00:13:48.576
Supposing him to be the Galactus.

00:13:48.832 --> 00:13:50.592
is all the heaven.

00:13:50.784 --> 00:13:52.192
We can desire.

00:13:52.448 --> 00:13:59.424
Thank you for listening, friends. this podcast was brought to you by Premier in association with Spurgeon's College.

00:13:59.392 --> 00:14:03.008
